review_blob: Pours with a rich, thick, sea shore-like head. Color is a delicious light amber. Aroma is an explosion of fruit and hop. Amazing taste, full of tropical fruit. Refreshing, slighly sweet, moderately hoppy. Crisp palate with a soft carbonation. Nice, extremely long finish.
beer_name: The Kernel India Pale Ale Mosaic

review_blob: Aroma is fresh, hoppy, fruity, and sparkly. Appearance is nothing special, but nice, clear, golden, amber. Head is large but doesnt last for too long. Taste is great. I imagine picking up pineapple, cucumber, orange, hops, other juicy stuff, and pine needles. Mouthfeel gives a medium body with an oily texture. Carbonation is fizzy, finish is fairly tangy. Overall a very nice beer, my favorite BrewDog after 5 AM Saint.

Appearance is pale, clear copper. Nice smooth head. Great aroma with wood, smoke, and a little hop. Taste is very malty with some hop. Slightly tangy aftertaste. A decent beer.

Rusty, flashy, and sparkly appearance. Very thick, porous head with a short lifetime. Extremely mild aroma. Taste is fruity with a little pine and hop. Sharp palate. A good beer, way better than the Hobgoblin.

---Rated via iPhone

Pours with a solid, white, thick head, which lasts for fairly long. Appearance is clear, color is copper. Mildly hoppy aroma. Surprisingly subtle but hoppy and slightly honey-like taste. Tangy aftertaste.

---Rated via iPhone

Not a great beer. Decent, slightly nutty aroma, and promising appearance, but downhill from there. Bland and muddy taste. Negligible palate. Love the brand, though.
